  <thing id="raPTMyHyTr" name="Hydra Traits" description="A hydra can be killed by severing all of its heads or slaying its body. Any attack that is not an attempt to sever a head affects the body, including area attacks or attacks that cause piercing or bludgeoning damage. To sever a head, an opponent must make a sunder attempt with a slashing weapon targeting a head. A head is considered a separate weapon with hardness 0 and hit points equal to the hydra&apos;s HD. To sever a head, an opponent must inflict enough damage to reduce the head&apos;s hit points to 0 or less. Severing a head deals damage to the hydra&apos;s body equal to the hydra&apos;s current HD. A hydra can&apos;t attack with a severed head, but takes no other penalties.{br}{br}{b}Note{/b}: There is a selector on the in-play tab to record the number of heads chopped off (negative numbers) or re-grown above the starting number (positive numbers)." compset="RaceSpec" summary="Foes can sunder heads to sever them, at 0 heads the hydra dies.">
    <fieldval field="actUserMin" value="0"/>
    <fieldval field="actUserMax" value="0"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra" name="Extraordinary Ability" abbrev=" (Ex)"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec" name="Show Spec" abbrev="Show Spec"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="UserAdjust" name="UserAdjust" abbrev="UserAdjust"/>
    <eval phase="PreLevel" priority="6000" index="2">~we have fast healing equal to the number of heads

      ~minimum 5
      var bonus as number
      bonus = maximum(field[abValue2].value, 5)

      #applydr[raPTHyFaHe, bonus]</eval>
    <eval phase="PreLevel" priority="6000" index="3"><![CDATA[
      ~we have bite attacks equal to the number of heads

      ~apply a minimum of 1, since Value.0 is undefined
      var bonus as number
      bonus = maximum(field[abValue2].value, 1)

      perform hero.childfound[wBite].assignstr["Value." & bonus]]]></eval>
    <eval phase="PreLevel" priority="6000" index="4">~ we have a natural armor of +6 at our starting HD of 5, +1/extra HD
      ~ this only uses the base # of heads, not the current number

      var bonus as number
      bonus = field[abValue].value - 5

      hero.child[ArmorClass].field[tACNatural].value += bonus</eval>
    <eval phase="PreLevel" priority="5000"><![CDATA[
      ~we'll have the selector go from our number of HD down to the
      ~negative of our number of HD.

      ~the user can mark heads chopped off by applying a negative
      ~or heads regrown by marking a positive

      ~start with our racial HD
      field[abValue].value += root.field[rHitDice].value

      ~ Get the total number of 'bonus hit dice' we have
      foreach pick in hero where "thingid.cBonusHD"
        field[abValue].value += 1
        nexteach

      ~if we have any templates, add their hit dice into the calculations
      foreach pick in hero from BaseTempl
        field[abValue].value += eachpick.field[tmHitDice].value
        nexteach

      field[actUserMin].value -= field[abValue].value
      field[actUserMax].value += field[abValue].value

      ~calculate our current number of heads
      field[abValue2].value += field[abValue].value + field[actUser].value]]></eval>
    </thing>
